post_text: Congratulations! This is a very prestigious honor
shared_text:
SSA Davis-Monthan
April 16 at 12:12 PM 路

Congratulations to SSA D-M 8th graders Ciara Nelson and Brianna Robold! They were nominated for the 2020 Broadcom MASTERS (Math, Applied Science, Technology and Engineering for Rising Stars), a program of Society for Science & the Public.
Broadcom MASTERS is the nation's premier middle school STEM competition. Every year, society-affiliated science fairs across the United States nominate the top 10% of their 6th, 7th, and 8th grade participants to enter this prestigious competition. Ciara and Brianna earned their nomination from their participation in SARSEF (Southern Arizona Research, Science and Engineering Foundation.
Please share your encouragement for these awesome students in the comments below!

post_text:
3 Year Olds in our Tiger Lillies classroom are learning about three R's of sustainability: Reduce, Reuse, and Recycle.
This study not only offers opportunity for children to explore a topic that interests them but allows them to be more aware of the world around them.
Students learn to solve problems, sort recycling materials and what happens to the trash when it leaves the house.

On this #GivingTuesday, we want to take this opportunity to thank all our students, staff, parents, and community members who donate their time, effort and money helping those who need it, helping our school, or both!
If you are considering donating today, don't forget that if you are an AZ taxpayer, you can take advantage of the AZ School Tax Credit program. Your donations will go to benefit our students and pay for field trips, club activities, and more. Thank you for helping our school family do the best we can for our students!
Visit http://www.sonoranschools.org/donate.aspx for more information

post_text: Did you know that we offer free, full-day Kindergarten? A recent study from the University of Virginia found that "a full-day of kindergarten [versus half day kindergarten] made all students better off," and full-day kinder closes the literacy achievement gap between English-speaking and non-English speaking students by 70 percent. Read the study at: https://nces.ed.gov/pubs2015/2015019.pdf

post_text: Last week, the Explorer class got a visit from a dental hygienist! They learned how to keep their teeth healthy. They also learned that they have ten teeth on the bottom of their mouth, and then used Play-Doh to make replicas.
